getPath

public java.lang.String getPath()
Description copied from interface: ManagedFilePath
Returns the absolute path of this file, within its file system. This path is normalised, so that . and .. elements have been removed. Also, the path only contains / as its separator character. The path always starts with / The root of a file system has / as its absolute path.

resolve

public ManagedFilePath resolve(ManagedFilePath path)
This method transforms the given name to a path using this path as basis. If this path represents /a/b then resolve will return /a/b/name. The path given must be relative.
